# Sync versions - {{REPO_INFRA_NAME}}

When you modify `required_version` or `required_providers` in a versions.tf file, you MUST also update the Cursor rules to maintain consistency.

## Required actions

1. **After modifying versions.tf**: Update the "Reference versions" section in `.cursor/rules/competences/infra-general.mdc` with the new versions (terraform, azurerm, azapi, random, azuread, github, grafana, jq, time as applicable).

2. **After modifying .terraform-version or github_vars.json (TERRAFORM_VERSION)**: Update the Terraform version in `infra-general.mdc`.

3. **After modifying .tflint.hcl** (azurerm ruleset version): Update `infra-general.mdc`.

## Workflow

Version changes → Update versions.tf in all affected layers → Update .mdc files in .cursor/rules/competences/
